<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title></title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Letter from </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Rt Hon Theresa May MP, Home Secretary</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">, </span><br /><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">to the Chair of the Committee, </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">9 December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt; font-weight:bold">Detention of Filimone Lacanivalu</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">Thank you for your letter dated 15 November expressing your concerns about</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> the treatment of Mr Lacanivalu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">I recognise and value the immense sacrifice and contribution made by</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">members of our Armed Forces, including foreign and Commonwealth</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">personnel. Their contribution is reflected in the Immigration Rules and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">nationality legislation, which enable foreign and Commonwealth personnel to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">apply to naturalise as a British citizen after five years' service, or alternatively</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">to apply for settlement after four years' service.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">Foreign and Commonwealth military personnel are exempt from immigration</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">control while serving. On discharge, they are given a period of grace of 28</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">days to regularise their immigration status and can subsequently apply to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">settle here up to two years after leaving the military, although they are</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">expected not to have remained here in breach of immigration laws in that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">time. Mr Lacanivalu did not apply to regularise his stay in the UK for over two</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">years.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">Whilst immigration officials correctly applied the rules in this case, it is not</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">clear that Mr Lacanivalu's Army unit correctly explained to him the immigration</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">procedures on his discharge. In the light of the particular circumstances of this</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">case, I have personally intervened. Mr Lacanivalu was released from</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">detention on Friday 15 November and will shortly be granted Indefinite Leave</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">to Remain in the UK exceptionally outside the Immigration Rules.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">I instructed UK Visas and Immigration (UKVI) to complete an urgent review of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">all of the cases of those individuals identified as ex-HM Armed Forces who</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">are currently detained. The review identified a total of eight former British</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">Armed Forces personnel in detention. The majority of these (six) are pending</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">deportation following serious criminal offences and after obtaining a significant</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">custodial sentence. One further individual has been detained following</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">curtailment of exemption from immigration control due to drug abuse. The</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">individual in the remaining case was discharged from the Armed Forces in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">2010 following a failed drugs test. All individuals have been assessed and in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">each case continued detention is considered to be both justified and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">proportionate.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">You also asked for details of British Army veterans who have been granted</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">British citizenship as well as the number deported in the years since 2008; this</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">information is not available.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">The Rt Hon Theresa May MP</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">Home Secretary</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11.5pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>